  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Markets are caught between conflicting forces as geopolitical tensions drive safe haven demand while Iran ceasefire hopes reduce war premium, creating volatile risk-on/risk-off rotation. Bitcoin's push toward $70K amid $196M in short liquidations signals renewed crypto momentum, but rising 10Y yields and fading Fed cut expectations present headwinds for risk assets.",
    "regimeImpact": "The relief rally remains intact but faces critical test at key resistance levels, with CPI data on April 10 serving as the next major catalyst that could either extend the bounce or confirm bear market resumption.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Monitor BMNR $62,300 structural level closely as BTC approaches $70K resistance - consider tightening put ladder strikes if momentum continues",
      "Prepare for volatility around April 10 CPI print - current oversold relief may reverse sharply if inflation disappoints",
      "Watch HYG credit performance and VIX behavior around 25 regime line as geopolitical premium fluctuates with ceasefire developments"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Bitcoin testing $70K with massive short squeeze ($196M liquidated) suggests momentum building but needs sustained breakout for trend change",
